{{Infobox saint |name= Abbo of Auxerre |birth_date= |birth_name = |death_date= 3 December 860 |feast_day= 3 December |venerated_in= [[Auxerre]], [[Saint-Germain l'Auxerrois|St. Germain]]<ref>[http://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=666 ''Saint Abbo'' (Catholic Online)]</ref> |image= |imagesize=250px |caption= |birth_place= |death_place= |titles= Abbot, Bishop |canonized_date= |canonized_place= |canonized_by= |attributes= |patronage= |major_shrine= |suppressed_date= |issues= }}
'''Abbo of Auxerre''' was a [[Benedictine]] abbot and [[bishop of Auxerre]].
He had been a monk, and later abbot, of the [[Abbey of Saint-Germain d'Auxerre]], and succeeded his brother [[Heribald of Auxerre]] as bishop of Auxerre. He resigned from the see in 859. He assisted in the synod of Poncy in 860, and died on 3 December that year. He is not listed in the [[Roman Martyrology]], the official but incomplete list of saints recognized by the [[Roman Catholic Church]].<ref>''Martyrologium Romanum'' (Libreria Editrice Vaticana, 2001, {{ISBN|88-209-7210-7}})</ref> His biography is included in ''[[Les Petits Bollandistes]]''.
